<div style="page-break-before: always; padding: 50px 60px; font-family: 'Helvetica', 'Arial', sans-serif; color: #12323c;">
  <h1 style="margin-top: 0; font-size: 28pt; color: #1e88e5;">Legal Validity Summary</h1>
  <p style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 20px;">
    This section summarises why the attached England assured periodic tenancy agreement appears aligned with the
    post-reform private rented sector model. It is generated from the facts provided in the wizard and is designed to be
    read alongside the Certificate of Curation.
  </p>

  <div style="border: 1px solid #1e88e5; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 18px;">
    <h2 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: #0d47a1;">Core tenancy elements</h2>
    <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 18px; line-height: 1.6;">
      <li><strong>Parties captured:</strong> Landlord {{landlord_full_name}} and {{tenants.length}} tenant(s) with contact details.</li>
      <li><strong>Property:</strong> {{property_address}} {{#if property_type}}({{property_type}}){{/if}}.</li>
      <li><strong>Rent and structure:</strong> &pound;{{rent_amount}} per {{rent_period}} due {{rent_due_day}}; tenancy starts {{tenancy_start_date}} and is drafted without a fixed end date.</li>
      <li><strong>Possession model:</strong> The agreement states that possession depends on a lawful statutory ground and any court order required by law.</li>
      <li><strong>Tenant notice:</strong> The agreement ties tenant notice to the statutory requirements in force at the relevant time.</li>
      {{#if subletting_allowed}}<li><strong>Subletting:</strong> {{subletting_allowed}}.</li>{{/if}}
      <li><strong>Rent review:</strong> The agreement references the section 13 rent increase route or any replacement statutory route in force at the relevant time.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div style="border: 1px solid #1e88e5; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 18px;">
    <h2 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: #0d47a1;">Deposit and prescribed information</h2>
    <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 18px; line-height: 1.6;">
      {{#if deposit_scheme_name}}
        <li>Deposit of &pound;{{deposit_amount}} to be protected with <strong>{{deposit_scheme_name}}</strong>{{#if deposit_protection_date}} by {{deposit_protection_date}}{{/if}}.</li>
      {{else}}
        <li style="color: #c62828; font-weight: bold;">No deposit scheme selected. Protection within 30 days is legally required.</li>
      {{/if}}
      {{#if deposit_paid_date}}<li>Deposit due/paid on {{deposit_paid_date}}.</li>{{/if}}
      <li>Deposit cap check: {{#if deposit_amount}}The template enforces Tenant Fees Act limits based on the rent provided.{{else}}Amount missing - cannot validate cap.{{/if}}</li>
    </ul>

    {{#unless prescribed_information_served}}
    <div style="background: #fff3cd; border: 2px solid #ffc107; border-radius: 6px; padding: 12px; margin-top: 12px;">
      <p style="margin: 0; color: #856404; font-weight: bold; font-size: 11pt;">CRITICAL WARNING - Prescribed Information Not Confirmed</p>
      <p style="margin: 8px 0 0 0; color: #856404; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 1.5;">
        <strong>Legal Requirement:</strong> Prescribed information must be served to the tenant within 30 days of receiving the deposit (Housing Act 2004).
        <br><strong>Consequences of Non-Compliance:</strong>
        <br>- Court may order you to pay the tenant 1-3x the deposit amount in compensation.
        <br>- Deposit non-compliance can materially weaken the landlord's position in later possession or enforcement proceedings until corrected.
        <br>- Late or unproven service can create avoidable dispute risk.
        <br><strong>Action Required:</strong> Confirm prescribed information has been or will be served within the statutory deadline.
      </p>
    </div>
    {{/unless}}
  </div>

  <div style="border: 1px solid #1e88e5; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 18px;">
    <h2 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: #0d47a1;">Safety and statutory information</h2>
    <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 18px; line-height: 1.6;">
      <li>Gas safety certificate: {{#if gas_safety_certificate}}Confirmed provided{{else}}Not confirmed{{/if}}</li>
      <li>Electrical safety (EICR): {{#if electrical_safety_certificate}}Confirmed provided{{else}}Not confirmed{{/if}}</li>
      <li>EPC rating: {{#if epc_rating}}Confirmed as {{epc_rating}}{{else}}Not confirmed{{/if}}</li>
      <li>Smoke alarms: {{#if smoke_alarms_fitted}}Confirmed{{else}}Not confirmed{{/if}}; CO alarms: {{#if carbon_monoxide_alarms}}Confirmed{{else}}Not confirmed{{/if}}</li>
      <li>Right to Rent checks: {{#if right_to_rent_check_date}}Completed on {{right_to_rent_check_date}}{{else}}Date not recorded{{/if}}</li>
      <li>England written information or government guidance recorded: {{#if how_to_rent_guide_provided}}Recorded{{else}}Not confirmed{{/if}}</li>
      {{#if has_shared_facilities}}
        <li>HMO/shared clauses included{{#if hmo_licence_status}} (licence: {{hmo_licence_status}}){{/if}}.</li>
      {{/if}}
    </ul>

    {{#unless how_to_rent_guide_provided}}
    <div style="background: #ffebee; border: 2px solid #f44336; border-radius: 6px; padding: 12px; margin-top: 12px;">
      <p style="margin: 0; color: #c62828; font-weight: bold; font-size: 11pt;">IMPORTANT CHECK - England Written Information or Guidance Not Confirmed</p>
      <p style="margin: 8px 0 0 0; color: #c62828; font-size: 10pt; line-height: 1.5;">
        <strong>Position:</strong> Record any England written information or government guidance you provide for this tenancy route, where applicable.
        <br><strong>Risk if omitted:</strong>
        <br>- Missing prescribed information can create compliance and evidential risk.
        <br>- The landlord may later need to prove what written information or guidance was supplied to the tenant.
        <br>- Proof of delivery should be retained with the tenancy file.
        <br><strong>Action Required:</strong> Confirm what written information or guidance was given, when it was given, and how delivery was evidenced in the tenancy file.
      </p>
    </div>
    {{/unless}}
  </div>

  <div style="border: 1px solid #1e88e5; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 18px;">
    <h2 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0; color: #0d47a1;">Inventory and property care</h2>
    <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 18px; line-height: 1.6;">
      <li>Inventory: {{#if inventory_attached}}Schedule to be attached{{else}}Not confirmed{{/if}}</li>
      <li>Cleaning: The tenancy materials require the property to be returned to the recorded move-in standard, allowing for fair wear and tear, with additional cleaning or treatment only where reasonably needed.</li>
      {{#if inventory_schedule_notes}}<li>Notes: {{inventory_schedule_notes}}</li>{{/if}}
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p style="font-size: 10pt; color: #555; line-height: 1.6;">
    This summary is informational and based solely on the data provided. It is not legal advice. Landlords must ensure all
    statutory documents are served correctly and retain evidence of service in line with the Housing Act 1988, Tenant Fees
    Act 2019, Housing Act 2004, and related regulations.
  </p>
</div>
